            "Church with singular beauty that combines modern infrastructure with nature. It has a glass front, through which it is possible to observe the immense sea. Weddings of couples from different parts of the country take place here who come to get married in this church because due to its unique structure. This beautiful temple is ideal for attracting weddings, as there are many couples who come from big cities to unite their lives in the sacrament of marriage. It was previously built of wood, because it was deteriorating. It was changed with cement, in 2016 after the earthquake it was restructured through a project by Mr. Julio Caballero.",
            "Virgin Grotto of Monserrat",
            "The inhabitants of the commune are devoted to this virgin, so they carry out pilgrimages and processions, these festivities being in the month of November, for 3 days, in which there are some activities such as the balcony that takes place on the first day, then the public dance is held for its inhabitants to enjoy and finally its festivities culminate with events such as baptisms, traditional games.",
            "Community park",
            "It is a recreational space where tourists and the population can enjoy a moment with family and friends. It has recreational games such as: slide, slide, swing and the spinning wheel.",
            "La Rinconada tourist viewpoint",
            "Place where you can see a beautiful panoramic view of La Rinconada beach and the coastal profile that goes from La Entrada to the tip of Montañita, it has comfortable seats and an awning to protect from rain and sun, from here You can see the small fishing port and how the residents return from fishing.",
            "Art Gallery",
            "The project was born as little colored houses, designed by a couple from the United States who have lived for 9 years, Shell Spivey and Marsha Spivey, who have supported the community unconditionally by taking steps to carry out this spectacular project. It has 55 murals, that tell the history of the commune, almost the entire façade of the houses has a painting done by young artists who supported the project",
            "Monument to the whales",
            "Monument made in honor of the visit of the humpback whale, the commune is one of the specific places where these cetaceans can be observed, therefore, between visits to the landscapes that this commune has, the tourist will be able to observe the spectacle that humpback whales do. Humpback whales visit the Ecuadorian coast to mate, it is for this reason that people say that they listen to and observe the whales' dancing, as well as their whistling, being a way to get their partner's attention to be able to mate."
